data.meta_description: Maksim Chmerkovskiy and Peta Murgatroyd are now a family of five! The couple announced they welcomed their third child, a baby boy, and shared his name.
data.text:
Maksim Chmerkovskiy and Peta Murgatroyd are now a family of five!

On Friday, July 12, the "Dancing With the Stars" pro dancers announced on Instagram that they welcomed their third baby, a boy named Milan Maksim Chmerkovskiy, into the world.

"He is officially evicted from his mom and he is sooooo cute!!!! Birth details later but for now we wanted to let you all know that mom and baby are doing perfect, and delivery took around 47 seconds total! Exactly one push!" the couple said in their caption.

In the post, Chmerkovskiy and Murgatroyd shared a cute photo of their son laying on Murgatroyd's lap while Chmerkovskiy sat near her. The pic appeared to be taken at a hospital.

"Amazing!!! Congratulations on baby #3!! ‚ù§Ô∏è," "Full House" star Candace Cameron Bure, who competed on Season 18 of "DWTS," commented.

In another post, the couple shared a close up of their baby's face and revealed he was born at exactly 8:48 a.m. on Friday and weighs 8 pounds.

"The fam is complete ü•π," they said.

In February, Murgatroyd and Chmerkovskiy announced they were expecting another child when they shared a funny video on Instagram that showed the cute moment Murgatroyd told Chmerkovskiy that she was pregnant.

‚ÄúBabe, stop. No way," he replied shocked.

However, Chmerkovskiy said he was "happy" to be a dad again.

The couple's pregnancy news came just seven months after they had their second child, Rio.

The couple are now the proud parents of three sons ‚Äî Shai, 7, Rio, 1, and Milan.
